  "prompt": "What are some Yu-Gi-Oh! Apps?",
  "response": "There are several Yu-Gi-Oh! apps available that cater to different aspects of the game. Here are some popular ones:\n\n1. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Links**: A digital card game that allows players to duel using characters from the Yu-Gi-Oh! anime. It features a streamlined version of the rules and includes various events and missions.\n\n2. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Master Duel**: A more comprehensive digital card game that supports the standard Yu-Gi-Oh! rules. It offers a wide range of cards, deck-building options, and competitive play modes.\n\n3. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Neuron**: This app serves as a resource for duelists. It includes a life points calculator, a card database, a deck-building tool, and rules information, making it useful for both casual and competitive players.\n\n4. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Card Database Apps**: Various apps are available that offer a database of cards, including detailed descriptions, rulings, and images. One such app is \"Yu-Gi-Oh! Card Viewer.\"\n\n5. **DuelingBook**: While primarily a web-based platform, it also has mobile-friendly features that allow users to duel online, track life points, and create decks with custom rules.\n\n6. **Cardfight!! Vanguard - Yu-Gi-Oh! Edition**: While not directly affiliated with Yu-Gi-Oh!, some players use Vanguard apps to learn about future trading card game strategies.\n\n7. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Calculator Apps**: Various life points calculator apps can help players keep track of life points during duels (e.g., \"Yu-Gi-Oh! Life Points Calculator\").\n\n8. **Fan-Made Apps**: There are numerous unofficial apps created by the community that provide deck builders, trade (for physical cards), and other tools, although their quality and reliability can vary.\n\nKeep in mind that availability and features of these apps may change over time, so it's a good idea to check your app store for the latest information and user reviews.",
